    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "You mentioned that long lines are less version control friendly. Actually this is not true if you use git diff --color-words ;) Editors like emacs allow you to display physically long lines in a window (no need for scrolling to the right) by inserting 'soft' newlines using the visual-line-mode.  I use this to VC my latex files.\n"
